  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Displacement and emergency tracking in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The general objective of this project is to assist the Government of Burundi, in partnership with humanitarian agencies, to access a comprehensive system of information on the presence of internally displaced persons in the country, the needs of this vulnerable population, and emergency events occurring within the country in order to provide timely assistance. In order to do so, this proposed project aims to address the current gaps in humanitarian emergency response in Burundi by: (1) expanding current data collection capacity on internally displaced persons (IDPs) using the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) and (2) creating an Emergency Event Tracking system for rapid assessment following natural disasters and other displacement events.</narrative>
  </description>
